This project has a Graphify knowledge graph for `bhukhadan_core` at
`bhukhadan_core/graphify-out/`.

**Before broad codebase exploration**, prefer Graphify when available:
- `graphify query "<question>" --graph bhukhadan_core/graphify-out/graph.json`
- `graphify path "<A>" "<B>" --graph bhukhadan_core/graphify-out/graph.json`
- `graphify explain "<concept>" --graph bhukhadan_core/graphify-out/graph.json`
- `graphify god-nodes --graph bhukhadan_core/graphify-out/graph.json`

Use Read/Grep/Glob directly for:
1. Editing or debugging specific known files/lines
2. Spec Kit / focused tasks where the touch list is already known
3. When `bhukhadan_core/graphify-out/graph.json` is missing

- Open `bhukhadan_core/graphify-out/graph.html` for interactive visualization
- Read `bhukhadan_core/graphify-out/GRAPH_REPORT.md` for architecture hubs
- After substantial code changes: `graphify update bhukhadan_core` then
  `graphify cluster-only bhukhadan_core --no-label`
